## 📚 Progressive Documentation Loading

**CRITICAL**: Only load documents relevant to your current task. Do NOT load all docs at once. All docs live under `docs/`.

### Decision Tree: What to Read

**Start here:**
- Understanding overall architecture or starting new work → `docs/ARCHITECTURE_GUIDELINES.md` (navigation hub)

**Creating or modifying a service:**
- Setting up a new service from scratch → `docs/ADDING-NEW-SERVICES.md` ⚠️
  - Always follow the full checklist before opening a PR

**TypeScript & Imports:**
- tsconfig, strict mode, import aliases → `docs/TYPESCRIPT-CONFIG.md`
  - Critical: all imports must use `@service-name/*`, never relative paths

**Code Quality:**
- ESLint (flat config), Prettier, Husky, CI pipeline → `docs/CODE-QUALITY.md`
  - ESLint 9+ requires `eslint.config.js`, not `.eslintrc.js`

**Service Communication & Boundaries:**
- Inter-service HTTP, databases, env vars → `docs/SERVICE-BOUNDARIES.md`
  - One database per service — no cross-database queries

**Builds & Workflow:**
- Turborepo, builds, caching, CI → `docs/DEVELOPMENT-WORKFLOW.md`

**Project Structure:**
- Folder layout, naming conventions → `docs/MONOREPO-STRUCTURE.md`

**Package Management:**
- pnpm commands, workspace protocol → `docs/PACKAGE-MANAGER.md`

